commit.message: Throw SettingRangeException for invalid signed->unsigned casts.
Set the correct interface version and update ChangeLog.
Fix escaping of brackets in regex in CMakeLists.txt
Fixed regex in conanfile.py
Added CMakeLists.txt to dist targets
Added unit test for config_read()

Fixed some constness inconsistencies in lookup APIs.

Also check for NULL name in lookup functions.
Fixed various bugs in setting lookups by name/path.
Fixed incorrect auto-conversion between int and int64 in C++ library.
revert scanner.h and scanner.c to previous version. For scanner.l instead we keep new version.
Fixed inconsistent use of short vs. unsigned short in some APIs.
Few more build fixes.
updated with escaping characters \a\b\v
Fix windows build error yet again.
More Windows build fixes.
Fix Windows build errors.

Add logic to handle memory allocation failures.

More generically, this patch adds handling of fatal errors.
Memory allocation failures are currently the only type of
fatal error.

- New C API config_set_fatal_error_func() allowing caller
  to provide a fatal error handler.
- A default handler will write a message to stderr and then
  call abort().
- The C++ library installs an internal handler that throws
  std::bad_alloc
- Route all malloc/calloc/realloc requests through new
  wrapper functions libconfig_malloc(), libconfig_calloc(),
  libconfig_realloc(), which call the above and then check
  the return value. If it's NULL, they call the fatal error handler.
- Force the flex- and bison-generated code to call the libconfig
  alloc functions instead of their default ones.

commit.message:
Fix locale handling when building with cmake

* Add `check_symbol_exists` for locale handling (it was commented out before)
* Mac OS: use header "xlocale.h" for checks
* Apply the result of these checks not only to `libconfig`, but also `libconfig++`
* This fixes the build warning "No way to modify calling thread's locale!"
* This also fixes the memory leak on Mac OS as described in issue #212.
